=== Etymology ===
From French [[paradis]], from Latin [[paradisus]], from Greek [[παράδεισος]] ‘royal park, orchard’, from [[Avestan]] ''pairidaēza'' ‘walled enclosure’, from ''pairi'' ‘around’ + ''diz'' ‘form, shape’.

=== Proper noun ===
[[Category:English proper nouns]]
'''Paradise''' (''uncountable'')

#(''religion'') [[Heaven]].
#(''religion'') The [[Garden of Eden]].

====Synonyms====
*(''Heaven''): [[Heaven]]
*(''Garden of Eden''): [[Eden]], [[Garden of Eden]]

